---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Resources">

<div class="space-y-6">

  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Resources</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Curated tools, references, and projects worth your time.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">

    <!-- Mathematics Resources -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 border-t-4 border-t-blue-600 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-5">Mathematics</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-5">

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://www.desmos.com" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">Desmos</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">The graphing calculator that belongs in every math classroom. Intuitive, free, and genuinely beautiful.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://www.geogebra.org" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">GeoGebra</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Dynamic geometry, algebra, and calculus in one tool. Exceptional for visualizing transformations and constructions.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://www.wolframalpha.com" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">Wolfram Alpha</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">A computational engine that shows its work. Invaluable for checking answers and exploring mathematical ideas.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@3blue1brown" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">3Blue1Brown</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Visual, elegant explanations of deep mathematics. If you've never felt calculus or linear algebra click into place, start here.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://www.cemc.uwaterloo.ca" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">CEMC — University of Waterloo</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Canada's leading math enrichment centre. Free courseware, contests, and problem sets that actually challenge students.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://www.khanacademy.org/math" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">Khan Academy — Math</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Reliable, self-paced practice with instant feedback. Best used to consolidate skills, not replace thinking.</p>
        </li>

      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Computer Studies Resources -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 border-t-4 border-t-blue-600 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-5">Computer Studies</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-5">

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://www.python.org" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">Python.org</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">The official home of Python — documentation, tutorials, and downloads. The language of choice for learning and for industry.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://cs50.harvard.edu" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">CS50 — Harvard University</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">The world's most-watched introduction to computer science. Rigorous, free, and genuinely fun. A strong complement to any CS course.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://replit.com" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">Replit</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">A full development environment in the browser. No installation, no friction — just open a tab and start coding.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://github.com" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">GitHub</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Where code lives. Learning version control early is one of the most professional habits a student can develop.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">freeCodeCamp</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Structured, project-based web development curriculum. Entirely free, and you finish with a portfolio to show for it.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://scratch.mit.edu" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">Scratch — MIT</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Block-based programming from MIT. Deceptively powerful for teaching logic, events, and creative problem solving.</p>
        </li>

      </ul>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">

    <!-- My Projects -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 border-t-4 border-t-blue-600 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-5">My Projects</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-5">

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <a href="https://github.com/roderickmonk" class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm hover:text-blue-700">GitHub — roderickmonk</a>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">All projects are open source. Browse the code, fork it, break it, learn from it.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Sudoku Solver <span class="font-normal text-slate-400">(TypeScript)</span></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">A constraint-satisfaction solver that handles any valid Sudoku puzzle. A clean example of backtracking algorithms in action.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Trading Simulator <span class="font-normal text-slate-400">(Python)</span></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">A backtesting framework for evaluating trading strategies. Good territory for statistics and data analysis students.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Reinforcement-Learning Crypto Bot <span class="font-normal text-slate-400">(AI / RL)</span></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">A deep-RL agent (PyTorch) trained to trade cryptocurrency. Where calculus, statistics, and code converge.</p>
        </li>

      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Further Reading -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 border-t-4 border-t-blue-600 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-5">Further Reading</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-5">

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm italic">Building Thinking Classrooms <span class="font-normal not-italic text-slate-400">— Peter Liljedahl</span></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">The most practical book on math pedagogy in years. Evidence-based strategies for getting students actually thinking.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm italic">Weapons of Math Destruction <span class="font-normal not-italic text-slate-400">— Cathy O'Neil</span></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Essential reading for any student who will live and work with algorithms. Mathematics as a social justice issue.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm italic">AI: A Modern Approach <span class="font-normal not-italic text-slate-400">— Russell & Norvig</span></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">The definitive AI textbook. Dense, rigorous, and worth the effort for anyone serious about the field.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm italic">The Pragmatic Programmer <span class="font-normal not-italic text-slate-400">— Hunt & Thomas</span></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Timeless advice on writing good software and thinking like a professional engineer. Required reading for serious coders.</p>
        </li>

        <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm italic">Designing Data-Intensive Applications <span class="font-normal not-italic text-slate-400">— Martin Kleppmann</span></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">The best systems-design book available. Indispensable once you're building software that actually matters.</p>
        </li>

      </ul>
    </div>

  </div>

</div>

</Layout>
